# Semgrep ignore patterns.
#
# A project-level .semgrepignore replaces semgrep's built-in defaults, so the
# common vendored/generated paths are listed explicitly below to keep them out
# of the scan.

# --- Vendored / generated paths ---
node_modules/
build/
dist/
vendor/
.git/
.venv/
env/
.tox/
.mypy_cache/
*.min.js

# --- Project-specific accepted findings ---
# Print Job intentionally grants the "All" role read+create so any desk user can
# submit and view their own print jobs; the relaxed-permissions finding on this
# doctype is accepted (see PR discussion).
print_bridge/print_bridge/doctype/print_job/print_job.json
